<br>
&quot;-does it work vs. shielded or shieldERs AC?&quot;<br>
<br>
Shielded AC and avoidance is taken into consideration. 2 rogues were dueling with 1 sitting on the ground all the time her back to the other rogue. I was facing the attacker and did /shield on the sitting rogue. I got hit and backstabbed on every single attack he made.<br>
<br>
&quot;-does it generate aggro when used? (i.e. vs. a normally nonkos mob)&quot;<br>
<br>
i dont think so, i shielded the MA before he started attacking for fun and i didnt draw aggro at all.<br>
<br>
&quot;-is the damage taken affected at all by mitigation or avoidance of the shieldER?&quot;<br>
<br>
probably not. No dodge/no miss/nothing from our AA either. It looks like a plain 75%-(AC/x) part of the damage. However, perhaps the AC on your shield (in hand) is added to the shielded person's AC (which could lower the damage a little bit). I only had a 23 AC shield to test and 12 seconds at once isnt exactly rocket science as far as results go.<br>
<br>
&quot;-does it trigger shieldER's damage shield?&quot;<br>
<br>
yes, you can double stack the DSes for 12 seconds before the mob is slowed <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
&quot;-does facing/elevation/etc. make any difference?&quot;<br>
<br>
i was facing a backstabbing rogue, so i kind of believe it doesnt affect in any way<br>
<br>
&quot;-does the AC of an equipped shield make any difference in mitigation, or just the act of equipping one?&quot;<br>
<br>
it didnt seem to make a big difference if any. Now the fact that the rogue was sitting on the ground wasnt helping my case exactly <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
