Drinal <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uwilorbaneslayer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>WilorBaneslayer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/18/02 9:47:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2238.topic&index=54>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_ac.gif" align=absmiddle>  Some other tests</span><hr size=1> I was testing it out last night and have these observations (some may be making more plain what has already been said):<br>
<br>
Damage is based on the Shielded's AC not yours.<br>
<br>
Range is very tight, I had to be in Melee range to /shield.  More like 10 feet than the previously reported 15 feet or you get &quot;soandso is too far away to be shielded&quot;<br>
<br>
You can shield and attack the person you are shielding (which is great for finding out hard data on things like Damage Mitigation from shields because you get pure damage numbers).<br>
<br>
Again, it does not stack with Disciplines on either side and it does not stack with other people shielding the same target.  But it is a free ability with a 3 minute reset timer.  <br>
<br>
The biggest limitation on this ability is the range component.  Range is so touchy you can't even do a /shield on the MT if you are behind most Boss Mobs and they are in front unless you are inside the mob.<br>
<br>
The good news is that with raid buffs, you will most probably be able to take 12 seconds of flurry damage at 75% and not die without an immediate Cheal.  This argues against buying up to the 36 second level in PoP, btw, because you may not be able to take 36 seconds of flurry damage at 75% unless you do get a prompt Cheal.  24 seconds seems to me to be the ideal amount of time to suck up damage without a prompt Returning To Bind Point.  So when PoP comes out, I do not recommend buying it up to max.  If we have no choice in the matter and it goes up in length automatically with your level, then getting high AC shields is a must and thank goodness we'll also be increasing our HPs as well.<br>
<br>
<br>
The range limitations argue that the most use you will get out of this is in groups where you have casters that pull agro.  Shield + AE Taunt should keep that caster alive and get the mob back to you pronto.<br>
<br>
Now I need to find a shield and start logging damage numbers so we can know how mitigation works - percentage?  1 AC = -1 Damage?    That's the big mystery at the moment. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ubobbfrommn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bobbfrommn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/18/02 11:20:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2238.topic&index=55>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_ac.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Some other tests</span><hr size=1> why me picturing havin a sheild cycle to get CH cycle goin....<br>
